description:
Alex James, former bassist of rock band Blur, and Matt Stone, one of Australia's youngest and most notable chefs, take you on a rocking tour of Australia's Margaret River. United by their love of food, the duo are off to discover the local food scene and draw inspiration from their travels to whip up some unique recipes. The guys throw themselves into their work, getting down and dirty as they hive-hunt for honey, scour the beaches for abalone, and even catch their own dinner! At the Margaret River Gourmet Escape, they meet renowned chefs such as Alex Atala, Alvin Leung, Kylie Kwong, Heston Blumenthal, Rene Redzepi and Tetsuya Wakuda.

From Yallingup to the beachside town of Prevelly, follow Alex and Matt on a culinary journey like no other and experience the beauty of a region renowned for its lush vineyards, pristine beaches, and premium gourmet produce.




Recipes That Rock - Season 1, Episode 1



At the famous Leeuwin Estate where Matt trained, Matt reunites with his first boss, Denis Horgan. Matt makes a delicious meal of freshly-caught marron, and a fennel and mayo salad with fresh herbs. After a short drive to Yallingup, one of the world's great big wave surfing destinations, they catch up with a friend, Josh Whiteland, who takes them to collect fresh abalone for Josh's Mexican spiced abalone with avocado and mango salad. Alex pays a visit to local luthier, Scott Wise and the two talk guitars and ukuleles, musician to musician.
